<h2>Event in January 2018</h2>
<strong>Severe winterstorm</strong>
A severe winterstorm passed over Western- and Central Europe in the middle of the month. Extreme winds tore across Western Europe on January 17 to 19, damaging buildings in the UK, the Netherlands, Belgium, Luxembourg, France, Germany, Poland, and the Czech Republic. There were reported instances of winds blowing roofs off buildings and the BBC reports that eight people including two firefighters have been killed in storm-related accidents. It was the strongest storm since 2007.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/jan2018/Analyse_2018011712.bmp"><img alt="" src="../images/jan2018/Analyse_2018011712.bmp" width="250px"></a>
<a href="../images/jan2018/Analyse_2018011812.bmp"><img alt="" src="../images/jan2018/Analyse_2018011812.bmp" width="250px"></a>
<br><br>
<em>Figure 1: Weather maps of 17th (left) and 18th January 2018 (Source: KNMI).</em>
<br><br>
<br><br>
The UK was first hit by gusts of up to 130 km/h during the overnight hours of January 17 to 18. In Germany, wind speeds reached 203 km/h in mountainous regions and up to 138 km/h in low-lying areas. Over Europe the storm left as many as 140,000 homes without power and caused travel chaos as it brought down trees onto rail lines and roads, forced bridges to close, and disrupted flights and train and ferry services.
<br><br>
<strong>Extreme rain- and snowfall amounts</strong>
Throughout the month of January several episodes of heavy rain and snow occurred over Western- and Central Europe. Especially France, Germany, the Alps and parts of the UK extreme amounts of rain felt with sums up to 250 mm. In the Alps this lead to several meters of fresh snow in large areas. During the period from January 17 to 25 the highest rainfall totals occurred along the Seine River east of Paris. Total rainfall greater than 180 mm occurred in this area where the Seine River flows toward Paris, causing severe flooding in many places.
<br><br>
<br><br>
<a href="../images/jan2018/Analyse_2018012500.bmp"><img alt="" src="../images/jan2018/Analyse_2018012500.bmp" width="250px"></a>
