<h2>The weather in January 2018</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
In January 2018 most of Europe was warmer than the reference period 1981-2010. Only some parts of Scandinavia showed cooler than normal temperatures. The northern side of the Alps reached new temperature records for January. In Switzerland it was the warmest January since the beginning of measurement in 1864. Monthly mean temperature in Geneva reached the all-time record of 6.0 Â°C which is +1.5 &#176;C above the old record. In Austria this January belongs to the warmest (rank 3) of the 251-year history of temperature measurements with a deviation of +3.8 &#176;C. Due to the warmth a persistent snow cover existed only above altitudes of 500 - 800 m.
As suggested in the figures, northern Europe and the Arctic were also warmer than normal. In the European territory of Russia at Arhangelsk (northeast Russia) the monthly mean temperature deviation from the long term mean was +8.8 &#176;C. At Svalbard airport a monthly mean temperature of -5.5 &#176;C (9.8 &#176;C above normal) was registered.
